	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville&#44; Kentucky</placeName>&#44; <date>February 17&#44; 1851</date></p>
				<p>Most honored <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hope that you have already received my letter and the<lb/> newspapers dispatched to you several days later.  I write this letter<lb/> only to prove to you that&#44; in spite of all my trouble and my small<lb/> persuasive powers&#44; I could do very little up to now&#44; For the &#8220;Advocate<add>&#63;</add><lb/> I have obtained&#44; outside of myself&#44; only two others&#44; among them <persName>Mr.<lb/> Bernas</persName>.  Still&#44; I have no doubt that after this newspaper appears<lb/> and answers the need of the time&#44; I shall find more subscribers<lb/> for it.  for the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#44; I have four new ones&#44; perhaps even<lb/> five.  On the other hand&#44; it seems to me that others because of<lb/> economy&#44; <del>be</del> intend to discontinue it.  In general&#44; the people here<lb/> are too uncultured&#44; to value such an undertaking&#44; or even<lb/> merely to understand it.  Those who do understand it are<lb/> too indifferent and too cold towards religion and Judaism<lb/> to have any interest toward such publications.  Such&#44; here<lb/> <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName>&#44; is usually the case.  In the course of the last d<add>&#63;</add><lb/> I have sold fourteen to fifteen prayer books for you.  <add>&#63;</add><lb/> these&#44; six for the congregation and several for Christians.  I<lb/> ask you to send them as soon as possible.  You may send two doz<lb/> in ordinary binding and two of the finest.  Send them to me<lb/> address at as low a price as possible&#44; less sending them.  Please<lb/> let me know.  In the meantime&#44; I shall collect for the &#8220;Oc<lb/>cident&#8221; for I have neglected to do so while looking for sub&#45;<lb/>scribers.  After delivering the prayer books&#44; I shall send you as<lb/> much money as possible.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Looking forward to your immediate reply&#44; I sign</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Most respectfully&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your most obedient servant and friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">B. H. Gotthelf</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
